Figure 1:Overview of Tiered Language Models.Top:The same released weights support a public configuration𝒞pub\mathcal{C}_{\mathrm{pub}}and a private configuration𝒞K\mathcal{C}_{\mathrm{K}}.
Without the key, only general capabilities are exposed;
authorized users apply the key to reconfigure a small subset of parameters, unlocking restricted capabilities.Bottom:Training pipeline. Pretraining runs next-token prediction using the public configuration, with everynn-th step including a backward pass through the keyed configuration. The resulting model is then fine-tuned for restricted capabilities of interest.
